== Chart performance ==
''Just Listen'' entered the Korean Monthly Album Chart at #22, with "lukewarm" sales of 13,986<ref>{{cite web | title=MIAK: Album Sales in March 2003 | publisher=Music Industry Association of Korea | url=http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200303.htm | accessdate=2007-05-22 | language=Korean |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070927031007/http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200303.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-27}}</ref> However, it started to gain popularity and rose to a peak of #4, which the album held for two consecutive months<ref>{{cite web | title=MIAK: Album Sales in April 2003 | publisher=Music Industry Association of Korea | url=http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200304.htm | accessdate=2007-05-22 | language=Korean |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070927031312/http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200304.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=MIAK: Album Sales in May 2003 | publisher=Music Industry Association of Korea | url=http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200305.htm | accessdate=2007-05-22 | language=Korean |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070927032919/http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_200305.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-27}}</ref> The album was #10 on the 2003 year-end chart, with total sales of 212,317 copies.<ref>{{cite web | title=MIAK: Album Sales in 2003 | publisher=Music Industry Association of Korea | url=http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_2003_2h.htm | accessdate=2007-05-22 | language=Korean |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070516070839/http://www.miak.or.kr/stat/kpop_2003_2h.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-05-16}}</ref>

